  "text": "Sc is not detected. During synthesis of PrP C the protein is subject to a number of post-translational modifications resulting in the mature protein. Direction of the protein to the ER by its 22 amino acid N-terminal signal sequence results in cleavage of the N-terminal signal peptide along with removal of a 23 amino acid C-terminal signal during which a GPI anchor is added. Asn-linked oligosaccarides are also attached in the ER and these saccharides are further modified in the Golgi network to become endoglycosidase H resistant. The GPI anchor, which is modified by the addition of sialic acid in the Golgi compartments, facilitates the trafficking of PrP C to the cell surface where endocytosis can occur [CITATION_1] .",
